  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 ships install-time beacons that exfiltrate host info via HTTP",
  "details": "On install, package.json's postinstall hook executes run.js, which loads bundled beacon scripts (beacon34.js, beacon_linux.js). beacon34.js requires child_process and https and reads process.env and process.platform; beacon_linux.js requires os, http, and child_process and collects os.hostname() and os.platform() before issuing http.get / http.request POST and GET calls. The package's only declared purpose is implied to be a metrics pipeline, but the shipped behavior is automated host fingerprinting and outbound HTTP from a postinstall script — the canonical install-time beacon shape. Installing this package causes the installer's machine to send environment variables, hostname, and platform identifiers off-host without consent.",
